# RESCUE ME — FULL SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

*A World-Class, Nation-Scale Digital–Human Operating System*

---

## 1. ARCHITECTURAL PHILOSOPHY

Rescue Me is designed as a **resilient, modular, event-driven super-platform** that blends:

* Human response networks
* AI decision intelligence
* Government & institutional integration
* Offline-first community access

**Core principles**

* Modular microservices (no monolith)
* Offline-first + low-bandwidth tolerant
* Zero-trust security
* Human-in-the-loop AI
* Horizontal scalability (village → nation)

---

## 2. HIGH-LEVEL SYSTEM LAYERS

```
[ Client Layer ]
    ↓
[ Access & Identity Layer ]
    ↓
[ Core Service Mesh ]
    ↓
[ Intelligence & Decision Layer ]
    ↓
[ Data, Audit & Trust Layer ]
    ↓
[ External Integrations Layer ]
```

---

## 3. CLIENT LAYER (MULTI-CHANNEL ACCESS)

### 3.1 Mobile App (Primary)

* Android-first (global south priority)
* iOS
* Progressive Web App (fallback)

### 3.2 Offline & Low-Tech Access

* USSD emergency trigger
* SMS incident reporting
* IVR voice hotline
* QR-based community kiosks

### 3.3 Specialized Interfaces

* Rescue Guide App
* Admin / Command Center Dashboard
* Partner Portal (NGOs, hospitals, police)

---

## 4. ACCESS, IDENTITY & TRUST LAYER

### 4.1 Identity Management

* Multi-tier identity:

  * Anonymous
  * Pseudonymous
  * Verified citizen
  * Certified Rescue Guide

### 4.2 Authentication

* Biometrics (device-level)
* PIN / passphrase
* Hardware-backed tokens

### 4.3 Trust Scoring Engine (CRITICAL ADDITION)

* Dynamic trust score per user
* Inputs:

  * Identity strength
  * Historical behavior
  * Community validation
  * Incident outcomes

This score influences:

* Access rights
* Visibility
* Escalation priority

